{"cursor":"8132","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\nIn linear algebra, a 'minor' of a matrix 'A' is the determinant of some smaller\nsquare matrix, cut down from 'A' by removing one or more of its rows or columns.\nMinors obtained by removing just one row and one column from square matrices\n('first minors') are required for calculating matrix cofactors, which in turn\nare useful for computing both the determinant and inverse of square matrices.\n","linknr":183,"url":"Minor_(linear_algebra)","recorded":1362553787,"links":28,"instances":["matrix_theory","mathematics","mathematics"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Matrix theory","Determinants"],"headings":["Detailed definition","Nomenclature","Cofactors and adjugate or adjoint of a matrix","Example","Complement","Applications","Multilinear algebra approach","See also","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/math/7/b/6/7b645327526717b5c31a54a789bf792e.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/3/f/5/3f5c2191d5128f36ec6b726c77df3b06.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/7/c/9/7c97e631f0d3b2ea4800ee9e2b17889b.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/c/1/7/c178e191f21e12d7ee798da18c5fbb6d.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/6/f/4/6f4c10c5f7317eb9c56d0b5cfba41789.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/5/4/f/54f16d956d5c4373579d91593e41763e.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/0/6/9/0698bc0f2ff0208e7314253ba5219640.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/9/9/d/99d2053b50a232bc1b4ab90cba12b379.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/3/6/2/362991bbf8d8dbaefc3f4ee47bc7bee8.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/4/2/2/42247191ca0542f1a63aa1437f00e538.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/5/0/b/50b15660051ca8a6f581704d024051c9.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/0/1/c/01cd011325ee89198fa82101ad6f2956.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/7/c/3/7c366763c24f8a822630d33398196599.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/imag